<li><a href="http://www.burtoniana.org/books/1885-Arabian%20Nights/index.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.burtoniana.org/books/1885-Arabian%20Nights/index.htm" rel="nofollow"><i>The Book of the Thousand Nights and a Night</i> (ten volumes 1885)</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.burtoniana.org/books/1886-Perfumed%20Garden/index.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.burtoniana.org/books/1886-Perfumed%20Garden/index.htm" rel="nofollow"><i>The Perfumed Garden of the Shaykh Nefzawi</i> (1886)</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.burtoniana.org/books/1885-Arabian%20Nights/index.htm#supp" class="external text" title="http://www.burtoniana.org/books/1885-Arabian%20Nights/index.htm#supp" rel="nofollow"><i>The Supplemental Nights to the Thousand Nights and a Night</i> (six volumes 1886 – 1888)</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.burtoniana.org/books/1898-The%20Jew,%20The%20Gypsy%20and%20El%20Islam/index.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.burtoniana.org/books/1898-The%20Jew,%20The%20Gypsy%20and%20El%20Islam/index.htm" rel="nofollow"><i>The Jew, the Gypsy and El Islam</i> (1898)</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.burtoniana.org/books/1911-Sentiment%20of%20the%20Sword/index.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.burtoniana.org/books/1911-Sentiment%20of%20the%20Sword/index.htm" rel="nofollow"><i>The Sentiment of the Sword: A Country-House Dialogue</i> (1911)</a></li>
</ul>
<p>Burton also wrote a great number of <a href="http://www.burtoniana.org/minor/minor_works.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.burtoniana.org/minor/minor_works.htm" rel="nofollow"><i>journal and magazine pieces</i></a>, many of which have never been catalogued. Over 200 of these have been collected in PDF facsimile format at <a href="http://burtoniana.org" class="external text" title="http://burtoniana.org" rel="nofollow"><i>burtoniana.org</i></a>.</p>
<p><a name="Biographies_and_other_books_about_Burton" id="Biographies_and_other_books_about_Burton"></a></p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Richard_Francis_Burton&amp;action=edit&amp;section=13" title="Edit section: Biographies and other books about Burton">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Biographies and other books about Burton</span></h2>
<p>A number of biographies of Burton have been written. The following is a list of biographies or books inspired by Burton, concentrating on those which are recent or influential.</p>
<ul>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREF.5B.5BFawn_M._Brodie.7CBrodie.2C_Fawn_M..5D.5D1967"><a href="/wiki/Fawn_M._Brodie" title="Fawn M. Brodie">Brodie, Fawn M.</a> (1967). <i>The Devil Drives: A Life of Sir Richard Burton</i>. New York: <a href="/wiki/W._W._Norton_%26_Company" title="W. W. Norton &amp; Company">W. W. Norton &amp; Company</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Devil+Drives%3A+A+Life+of+Sir+Richard+Burton&amp;rft.aulast=%5B%5BFawn+M.+Brodie%7CBrodie%2C+Fawn+M.%5D%5D&amp;rft.au=%5B%5BFawn+M.+Brodie%7CBrodie%2C+Fawn+M.%5D%5D&amp;rft.date=1967&amp;rft.place=New+York&amp;rft.pub=%5B%5BW.+W.+Norton+%26+Company%5D%5D&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Richard_Francis_Burton"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFBurton1893"><a href="/wiki/Isabel_Burton" title="Isabel Burton">Burton, Isabel</a> (1893). <i><a href="http://burtoniana.org/biography/1893-Isabel-Life/index.html" class="external text" title="http://burtoniana.org/biography/1893-Isabel-Life/index.html" rel="nofollow">The Life of Captain Sir Richard F. Burton KCMG, FRGS</a></i>. <b>Vols. 1 and 2</b>. London: <a href="/wiki/Chapman_and_Hall" title="Chapman and Hall" class="mw-redirect">Chapman and Hall</a><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://burtoniana.org/biography/1893-Isabel-Life/index.html" class="external free" title="http://burtoniana.org/biography/1893-Isabel-Life/index.html" rel="nofollow">http://burtoniana.org/biography/1893-Isabel-Life/index.html</a></span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Life+of+Captain+Sir+Richard+F.+Burton+KCMG%2C+FRGS&amp;rft.aulast=Burton&amp;rft.aufirst=Isabel&amp;rft.au=Burton%2C+Isabel&amp;rft.date=1893&amp;rft.volume=Vols.+1+and+2&amp;rft.place=London&amp;rft.pub=%5B%5BChapman+and+Hall%5D%5D&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fburtoniana.org%2Fbiography%2F1893-Isabel-Life%2Findex.html&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Richard_Francis_Burton"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFEdwardes1963"><a href="/wiki/Allen_Edwardes" title="Allen Edwardes">Edwardes, Allen</a> (1963). <i>Death Rides a Camel</i>. New York: The Julian Press.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Death+Rides+a+Camel&amp;rft.aulast=Edwardes&amp;rft.aufirst=Allen&amp;rft.au=Edwardes%2C+Allen&amp;rft.date=1963&amp;rft.place=New+York&amp;rft.pub=The+Julian+Press&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Richard_Francis_Burton"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFFarwell1963"><a href="/wiki/Byron_Farwell" title="Byron Farwell">Farwell, Byron</a> (1963). <i>Burton: A Biography of Sir Richard Francis Burton</i>. New York: <a href="/wiki/Penguin_Books" title="Penguin Books">Penguin Books</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Burton%3A+A+Biography+of+Sir+Richard+Francis+Burton&amp;rft.aulast=Farwell&amp;rft.aufirst=Byron&amp;rft.au=Farwell%2C+Byron&amp;rft.date=1963&amp;rft.place=New+York&amp;rft.pub=%5B%5BPenguin+Books%5D%5D&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Richard_Francis_Burton"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
